In a cinematic landscape dominated by superheroes and supernatural powers, Solomon emerges as a rare gem—a riveting movie series that celebrates raw humanity, unflinching courage, and the enduring spirit of justice.

At the heart of the series is Solomon, a man without powers, riches, or political influence, yet endowed with something far greater: a fierce resolve to fight for the voiceless. From bustling city streets to the darkest alleyways, Solomon defends orphans, the homeless, and the less privileged, confronting powerful forces that prey on the weak—regardless of their status or connection.

But Solomon’s battle isn’t without scars.

His journey is deeply personal. He lost his father—a local activist and role model—in the line of fire while standing up for their community. His sister, now blind from a traumatic incident tied to their family’s crusade, remains his emotional anchor and constant reminder of the cost of justice. Despite the pain, Solomon pushes forward, a one-man army driven not by vengeance, but by love and duty.

What sets Solomon apart is its realism. There are no capes, no superpowers—just grit, loyalty, and an unwavering commitment to doing what’s right. The series powerfully illustrates how courage doesn’t always come with fame, and that real heroes often go unseen.

With a compelling narrative, grounded performances, and themes that echo the societal struggles of many communities today, Solomon is more than just entertainment—it’s a movement. snippet.title: Send Help | Official Trailer | In Theaters Jan 30
snippet.description:
Rachel McAdams. Dylan O’Brien. SEND HELP.

Directed by Sam Raimi, only in theaters January 30, 2026.

20th Century Studios’ Send Help, the upcoming darkly comedic psychological thriller from genre-bending visionary director Sam Raimi (Spider-Man, The Evil Dead).

The all-original film stars Oscar® and Tony Award® nominated actress Rachel McAdams (Spotlight, Are You There God? It's Me, Margaret., Mean Girls), Dylan O’Brien (Twinless, Saturday Night), Edyll Ismail (La Brea), Dennis Haysbert (Far from Heaven), Xavier Samuel (Elvis), Chris Pang (Crazy Rich Asians), Thaneth Warakulnukroh (Thai Cave Rescue), and Emma Raimi (Happy Pills), and releases in theaters nationwide on January 30, 2026. 

Linda Liddle (Rachel McAdams) and Bradley Preston (Dylan O’Brien), two colleagues who find themselves stranded on a deserted island after they are the only survivors of a plane crash. On the island, they must overcome past grievances and work together to survive, but ultimately, it becomes an unsettling and darkly humorous battle of wills and wits to make it out alive. 

“I’ve always loved stories where interesting, dynamic characters are pushed to extremes,” says director Sam Raimi. “In our story, the power shifts create an escalating situation that’s brimming with unexpected turns and suspense.” 

Send Help is produced by Raimi and Zainab Azizi (65), executive produced by JJ Hook (The Amateur), and written by Damian Shannon & Mark Swift (Friday the 13th, Baywatch), with original music by Danny Elfman (The Nightmare Before Christmas, Batman).
